cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a method for few-shot learning using deep learning models, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. Specifically, the paper focuses on addressing the overfitting issue in deep learning models when dealing with low data regimes. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of "cs.LG" (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper conducts experiments on image datasets, indicating that it may also belong to the sub-category of "cs.CV" (Computer Vision). The paper also proposes a new method for weight initialization and retraining, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-categories of "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) and "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its method on few-shot classification tasks, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of "cs.CL" (Computation and Language).
